What you see is a chhaupadi hut in rural Nepal, where girls and women are sent to while on their period. This story marks the launch of @tabooglobalperiods ‚Äì our ongoing project that uncovers the implications of menstruation in the lives of teenagers around the globe üåé‚Å†

We‚Äôre on a journey to change the way periods affect our lives, our bodies and our environment üë£ there's a few things we strongly stand for:‚†Ä

The most used method of period management in Ghana is the 'homemade alternative' ‚Äì usually consisting of old rags. Sometimes unhygienic materials such as mud, leaves, animal skin and even dung are also used. In an effort to counter these ineffective and uncomfortable period management options, @marinatricks_ and @peaceley visited two rural schools in the Volta region and distributed 12 OrganiCups üá¨üá≠ 25 more will be distributed in December.
